Paige - Project Manager at Hendericks Building (Sister)

Paige, age 27. She works in a corporate role earning between $70,000 and $80,000 per year. 
She and her fiance, who earns about $100,000 annually by herself. 
Recently purchased a starter home and are currently planning a wedding that will cost around $35,000. 
They are sharing wedding expenses and receiving some help from family. 
Although their combined income provides stability, Paige feels some financial stress due to the high cost of the wedding and the responsibility of managing a mortgage at the same time.

Paige and her fiance make financial decisions together rather than having one person take full control. 
In the short term, her goal is to complete the wedding without unnecessary debt. 
In the long term, she hopes to move into a larger home, purchase a new car, and eventually start a family. 
She recently has paid off her school debt goal. Because of these goals, understanding where their money goes each month is very important to her future. 
She does not currently use a budgeting app but is highly comfortable with technology, as is her fiance. 
A financial management system that allows shared access, tracks spending categories clearly, and shows progress toward savings goals would help reduce her stress and support their future plans.
